parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks while accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle makes unusual noises
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle hesitates or jerks while accelerating
the check engine light comes on
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power or acceleration can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
the check engine light comes on
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag to deploy can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a front-end collision.
symptoms: The "airbag off" or "passenger airbag off" light remains on
indicating that the airbag will not deploy in the event of a crash
even when an adult passenger is seated in the front passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim headlight failure can cause a visibility hazard for the driver, making it difficult to see the road at night, dawn, or dusk, which can lead to accidents and potentially cost lives.
symptoms: The headlights on the dim setting are extremely dim
failing to properly illuminate the roadway
making it difficult to see the road at night
dawn
or dusk
requiring the use of bright lights
which can be dangerous and illegal when meeting oncoming traffic.
